\angle DHE &= 360^\circ - \angle HEC - \angle ECD - \angle CDH \\
&= 360^\circ - 90^\circ - \angle ACB - 90^\circ\\
&= 180^\circ - \angle ACB.
\end{align*} From triangle $ABC$, we have $180^\circ - \angle ACB = \angle BAC + \angle ABC = 46^\circ + 71^\circ = \boxed{117^\circ}$

